EUROPEAN FOULBROOD, APIS - EUROPE (04): NORWAY (AUST-AGDER) OIE
***************************************************************
A ProMED-mail post
http://www.promedmail.org
ProMED-mail is a program of the
International Society for Infectious Diseases
http://www.isid.org

Date: 4 Jul 2017
Source: OIE, WAHID [edited] http://www.oie.int/wahis_2/public/wahid.php/Reviewreport/Review?page_refer=MapFullEventReport&reportid=24200


European foulbrood of honey bees, Norway
----------------------------------------
Information received on [and dated] 4 Jul 2017 from Dre Kristina Landsverk, Chief Veterinary Officer, Norwegian Food Safety Authority, Ministry of Agriculture and Food, Brumunddal, Norway

Summary
Report type: immediate notification
Date of start of the event: 27 Jun 2017
Date of confirmation of the event: 3 Jul 2017
Reason for notification: reoccurrence of a listed disease
Date of previous occurrence: 25 Apr 2017
Manifestation of disease: sub-clinical infection
Causal agent: _Melissococcus plutonius_
Nature of diagnosis: laboratory (advanced)
This event pertains to a defined zone within the country.

New outbreaks (1)
Summary of outbreaks: Total outbreaks: 1
Outbreak 1: Grimstad, Vatnestrand, Agder Department, South & West Region, Aust-Agder
Date of start of the outbreak: 27 Jun 2017
Outbreak status: continuing (or date resolved not provided)
Epidemiological unit: apiary
Affected animals:
Species / Susceptible / Cases / Deaths / Killed and disposed of / Slaughtered
Bees (hives) / 17 / 1 / - / - / -
Affected population: One of the "hives" was a swarm of bees in the apiary.

Outbreak statistics [rates apparent, expressed as percentages]
Species / Morbidity rate / Mortality rate / Case fatality rate / Proportion susceptible animals lost*
Bees (hives) / 5.88 / ** / ** / **
* Removed from the susceptible population through death, destruction, and/or slaughter
** Not calculated because of missing information

Epidemiology
Source of the outbreak(s) or origin of infection: unknown or inconclusive
Epidemiological comments: Samples from environment in apiary. Same disease at the same place as in 2011.
Control measures
Measures applied: surveillance within containment and/or protection zone, quarantine; vaccination permitted (if a vaccine exists); no treatment of affected animals
Measures to be applied: stamping out, disinfection

Diagnostic test results
Laboratory name and type / Species / Test / Test date / Result
Norwegian University of Life Sciences (NMBU) (national laboratory) / Bees / bacteriological examination / 3 Jul 2017 / Positive

Future reporting
The event is continuing. Weekly follow-up reports will be submitted.

[The location of the outbreak can be seen on the interactive map included in the OIE report at the source URL above.]

